    "We therefore conjecture that poles in ∂φ(z) at non-insertion points can only exist at the zeroes ofJ + (z) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i).Stated differently, ∂ΦJ + is a conformal tensor and the zeroes of J + ensure that the places where ∂Φ behaves badly under conformal transformations do not ruin this fact.",
    "JHEP04(2024)048Let us introduce some useful notation.",
    "We will denote a correlation function weighted average of a field Ψ(z) asF Ψ (z):= Ψ(z) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i).",
    "(5.7)We show in appendix E that there is an exact factorisationF ∂ΦJ + (z) = F ∂Φ (z)F J + (z),which follows from the fact that ∂Φ(z) and J + (z) commute.",
    "Since ∂φ(z) = F ∂Φ (z), this factorisation along with (5.6) confirms that poles in ∂φ(z) away from insertion points can only occur at the zeroes of F J + (z).Recalling J + = ξ + η +, we will assume that J + (z) → 0 when either ξ + (z) → 0 or η + (z) → 0."
